\label{eqLogisticDiscrete}
y_t  \approx r y_{t-1} (1 - y_{t-1} ).
\end{equation}
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size large
Perhaps the most powerful and flexible method of estimation of the parameters, 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=\{r,K\}$
\end_inset

, is a state space representation where an additional observation model is added to connect observed indices 
\begin_inset Formula $O$
\end_inset

 to the unobserved and (usually unobservable) real system state 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

